*** SEARCH
***

*** MITM attack
*** A Participant has verified a message from another participant when he signed something different
search [1] init2 =>! {SSS:SamplePool}<(ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](sigRecord(ID1:Identifier, (sig(STR:StringMSG, R:Nat, P:Polynomial), SIGS:Set{Attribute})), ATTS:Set{Attribute})) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}]ATTS':Set{Attribute}) (ID3:Identifier[KS3:Set{Key}]((mIvS(ID1:Identifier,STR':StringMSG,[R':Nat, P':Polynomial]), ATTS'':Set{Attribute})))>net(MSGS:Msgs) such that STR =/= STR' .

eof

*** Signature search on init1
search [4] init1 =>! {SSS:SamplePool}<(ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID2:Identifier,STR:StringMSG,SIG:Pair), ATTS)) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ID1:Identifier =/= ID2:Identifier /\ ID2 =/= Eve .

*** Signature search on init2
search [4] init2 =>! {SSS:SamplePool}<(ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID2:Identifier,STR:StringMSG,SIG:Pair), ATTS)) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ID1:Identifier =/= ID2:Identifier /\ ID2 =/= Eve .

***
*** MODEL CHECKING & INVARIANT ANALYSIS
***

load model-checker.maude
load ./falcon-PREDS.maude
load ./falcon-CHECK.maude

*** TERMINATION
red modelCheck(init1, <> verifiedSignatureFrom(Bob, Alice)) .
red modelCheck(init2, <> verifiedSignatureFrom(Bob, Alice)) .

*** FAIRNESS
red modelCheck(init1, [] (wantsToSignAndSendTo(Alice, Bob) -> <> verifiedSignatureFrom(Bob, Alice))) .
red modelCheck(init2, [] (wantsToSignAndSendTo(Alice, Bob) -> <> verifiedSignatureFrom(Bob, Alice))) .

*** AUTHENTICATION
*** Definiton: Proof that the sender has the private key and signed the message.
*** Natural language: There is no path in which a message has been verified without it being signed at first by the other participant.
search [1] init1 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}]ATTS:Set{Attribute}) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier,STR:StringMSG,SIG:Pair), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((mI(ID1:Identifier,STR:StringMSG) in ATTS:Set{Attribute}) == false) .
search [1] init2 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}]ATTS:Set{Attribute}) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier,STR:StringMSG,SIG:Pair), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((mI(ID1:Identifier,STR:StringMSG) in ATTS:Set{Attribute}) == false) .

*** A way to prove authentication could be to prove that whenever a messgae is singed by someone 
*** then the receiver will verify it using the appropiate public key, proving the authenticity of the signature.

*** INTEGRITY
*** Definition: Proof that the message was not modified after the sign.
*** Natural language: There is no path of execution in which a message is different from the one used in the signature procedure.
search [1] init1 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](sigRecord(ID1:Identifier, (sig(STR:StringMSG,R:Nat,P:Polynomial), SIGREC:Set{Attribute})), ATTS:Set{Attribute})) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier, STR':StringMSG,[R:Nat,P:Polynomial]), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((STR:StringMSG =/= STR':StringMSG) == true) .
search [1] init2 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](sigRecord(ID1:Identifier, (sig(STR:StringMSG,R:Nat,P:Polynomial), SIGREC:Set{Attribute})), ATTS:Set{Attribute})) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier, STR':StringMSG,[R:Nat,P:Polynomial]), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((STR:StringMSG =/= STR':StringMSG) == true) .

*** Prove using model checking as from a given point forward the pair message/signature is not modified.

*** NON-REPUDIATION
*** Definition: Once the signature is made, the signer can not deny it.
*** Invariant: Store messages and signatures done by Alice. 
*** Check whenever a message has Alice's signature, then it was actually previously signed (there exist that signature in Alice's repository of signatures).
search [1] init1 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](sigRecord(ID1:Identifier, (sig(STR:StringMSG,R:Nat,P:Polynomial), SIGREC:Set{Attribute})), ATTS:Set{Attribute})) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier, STR:StringMSG,[R':Nat,P':Polynomial]), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((R:Nat =/= R':Nat) or (P:Polynomial =/= P':Polynomial)) .
search [1] init2 =>* {SSS:SamplePool}< (ID1:Identifier[KS1:Set{Key}](sigRecord(ID1:Identifier, (sig(STR:StringMSG,R:Nat,P:Polynomial), SIGREC:Set{Attribute})), ATTS:Set{Attribute})) (ID2:Identifier[KS2:Set{Key}](mIvS(ID1:Identifier, STR:StringMSG,[R':Nat,P':Polynomial]), ATTS':Set{Attribute})) PS:Participants >net(MSGS:Msgs) such that ((R:Nat =/= R':Nat) or (P:Polynomial =/= P':Polynomial)) .